commit.message:
Make error message more helpful

This makes it more clear that the 'overwrite' argument does not apply
to the mrcfile.open() function.

See https://github.com/ccpem/mrcfile/issues/59

Add tests for setting header origin field

These are passing for me. Added to check behaviour after bug report in
https://github.com/ccpem/mrcfile/issues/59

Update error handling in mrcmemmap

- Catch a wider range of possible errors
- Add alternative error message for Windows

Update builds

- Make very long s390x builds faster
- Only run Python 2.7 tests on FreeBSD
Remove build combinations with build errors
Remove Python 3.12 builds from unsupported architectures
Update GitHub Action for Python publishing

Fix numpy deprecation warning

Converting a single-item array to a scalar without extracting the item
first is deprecated from numpy 1.25.
Fix memory copy bug in numpy >= 1.24

Update docs to add supported MRC mode 12

https://github.com/ccpem/mrcfile/issues/56
Add Python 3.11 and numpy 1.24 to builds
Add info about indexed_extended_header to change log

Merge pull request #52 from dagewa/extended-header-unused-space-fix

Add indexed_extended_header property

This allows the indexed part to be a smaller size than the extended header itself, which wasn't possible before.
